ProtoResult:
. "A series $\sum f_n$ converges uniformly on a set $S$ if and
   only if for each $\epsilon>0$ there is an integer $N$ such 
   that $ \|f_n+f_{n+1}+\cdots+f_m\|_S<\epsilon m\ge n\ge N. $"
